  "body": "### Description\r\nPerforming an HTTP(S) POST to the Key Manager API of the Teku validator service for setting the fee recipient to the burn address for a specific validator pubkey results in a 400 Bad Request error: `{\"code\":400,\"message\":\"Cannot set fee recipient to 0x00 address.\"}`. What is the rationale for this? Is it possible to allow setting the burn address as fee recipient?\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\ncurl -k --cert-type P12 --cert <cert_file>:\"<cert_pass>\"  -X POST \"https:/<validator_container>:<validator_port>/eth/v1/validator/<pubkey>/feerecipient\" -H  \"accept: */*\" -H  \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d \"{\\\"ethaddress\\\":\\\"0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000000\\\"}\" -H \"Authorization: Bearer <token>\"\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:** [What you expect to happen]\r\nThe fee recipient should be set even if it is the burn address\r\n\r\n**Actual behavior:** [What actually happens]\r\nThe 0x00 address cannot be set as fee recipient for a validator\r\n\r\n### Versions (Add all that apply)\r\n`teku/v23.10.0/linux-x86_64/-eclipseadoptium-openjdk64bitservervm-java-17`\r\n\r\nRunning in Docker\r\n",
